1
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:38,200
[Too Young To Love]

2
00:01:38,470 --> 00:01:41,270
[Episode 6]

3
00:01:42,950 --> 00:01:44,840
Open your books to page 248.

4
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,460
Let's look at question 17.

5
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,000
15 points.

6
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:50,500
It's a freebie.

7
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,280
Just memorize it.

8
00:01:56,479 --> 00:01:57,229
Mr. Bu.

9
00:01:58,120 --> 00:01:59,720
Mr. Bu, I have a question too.

10
00:02:00,070 --> 00:02:01,400
Figure it out yourself.

11
00:02:01,870 --> 00:02:04,710
Sorry. The subscriber you dialed
is powered off.

12
00:02:04,870 --> 00:02:08,150
Sorry. The subscriber you dialed
is powered off.

13
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,590
Don't worry about Tong.

14
00:02:12,490 --> 00:02:13,300
[Have you reached Xiaole?]

15
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:17,270
[Reborn! We Got This]

16
00:02:13,590 --> 00:02:15,590
He promised emphatically

17
00:02:15,810 --> 00:02:18,120
he'd definitely show up
for tonight's band performance.

18
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:19,520
If we do well this time,

19
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:23,250
we might be able to perform there
regularly for the next few months.

20
00:02:27,750 --> 00:02:30,240
You really think you can become a star?

21
00:02:28,710 --> 00:02:29,829
[You really think you can become a star?]

22
00:02:29,850 --> 00:02:31,190
[Look at you. You're nowhere near
as good-looking as my idol.]

23
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:31,680
Look at you.

24
00:02:32,030 --> 00:02:34,690
You're nowhere near as good-looking
as my idol.

25
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,630
We're an independent band.

26
00:02:36,630 --> 00:02:40,120
We're nothing like your idol,
who's just famous for his face.

27
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:44,520
How about this?

28
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,470
Well,

29
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:48,240
I'll go to the office
and photocopy the study materials for you.

30
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:48,910
Okay?

31
00:02:49,190 --> 00:02:50,870
Then you guys behave yourselves.

32
00:02:50,870 --> 00:02:51,870
Don't run around.

33
00:02:52,079 --> 00:02:52,750
Be good.

34
00:02:53,079 --> 00:02:54,410
Wait for me to come back.

35
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:10,150
Come in.

36
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:12,120
Mr. Bu.

37
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:15,680
My stomach hurts a bit.

38
00:03:15,870 --> 00:03:18,530
Can I skip the next self-study class
and go home?

39
00:03:20,030 --> 00:03:22,690
Is it because you're worried
about Tong Xiaole?

40
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:25,430
That's part of it,

41
00:03:25,750 --> 00:03:28,079
but my stomach really does hurt.

42
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,870
I don't have any medicine

43
00:03:34,870 --> 00:03:35,800
for a stomachache.

44
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:36,680
However,

45
00:03:36,910 --> 00:03:39,800
I specially prepared some study materials
just for you.

46
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,630
Specially?

47
00:03:40,630 --> 00:03:41,240
Yes.

48
00:03:41,590 --> 00:03:42,430
For me?

49
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:43,190
Yes.

50
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:48,470
Because you're my most promising student.

51
00:03:49,079 --> 00:03:50,079
Most promising?

52
00:03:50,190 --> 00:03:51,750
So just go back

53
00:03:51,870 --> 00:03:53,310
for the next self-study class.

54
00:03:53,310 --> 00:03:54,360
As for Tong Xiaole,

55
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:55,520
I'll contact him.

56
00:03:56,310 --> 00:03:57,079
Okay.

57
00:03:57,079 --> 00:03:57,520
Go back now.

58
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:58,360
Okay.

59
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,910
Mr. Bu, I won't let you down.

60
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:04,470
Good.

61
00:04:14,430 --> 00:04:15,150
Chen Fan.

62
00:04:15,470 --> 00:04:16,240
What's wrong?

63
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:18,750
Mr. Bu, my throat...

64
00:04:20,310 --> 00:04:23,240
Is it also because you're worried
about Tong Xiaole?

65
00:04:26,070 --> 00:04:26,480
Here.

66
00:04:28,190 --> 00:04:29,870
I really don't have any medicine

67
00:04:29,870 --> 00:04:30,870
for a sore throat.

68
00:04:30,870 --> 00:04:31,680
However,

69
00:04:32,190 --> 00:04:34,430
I specially prepared some study materials
just for you.

70
00:04:34,430 --> 00:04:35,190
Specially?

71
00:04:35,310 --> 00:04:35,800
Yes.

72
00:04:36,430 --> 00:04:38,560
Because you're my most promising student.

73
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:39,490
Most promising?

74
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:39,920
Yes.

75
00:04:40,190 --> 00:04:42,590
Just go back
for the next self-study class.

76
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:43,560
Thank you, Mr. Bu.

77
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:44,750
I'll definitely study hard.

78
00:04:44,750 --> 00:04:45,190
Good.

79
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:36,100
Why haven't you come to class yet?

80
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,159
It's already noon.

81
00:05:39,190 --> 00:05:39,990
Where are you?

82
00:05:41,270 --> 00:05:42,390
Are you okay?

83
00:05:43,450 --> 00:05:46,900
[Reply soon]

84
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:44,950
Reply soon.

85
00:05:54,870 --> 00:05:55,310
Hello.

86
00:05:56,430 --> 00:05:58,240
Xiaole, you finally answered!

87
00:05:58,310 --> 00:06:01,570
We were all worried sick
because you didn't come to school.

88
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:03,630
I'm fine.

89
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:05,310
I just overslept.

90
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:08,120
Don't forget the band performance
at 7 PM tonight.

91
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:10,240
I'll wait for you at the venue
after class.

92
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:10,750
Okay.

93
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:12,680
I got it.

94
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:13,480
It's still early.

95
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:15,080
Don't worry. I won't be late.

96
00:06:16,190 --> 00:06:17,630
Dad, why are you back?

97
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:19,120
Why are you at home?

98
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:20,450
You didn't go to school?

99
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:23,430
Dad, I have something urgent.

100
00:06:23,430 --> 00:06:24,360
I'm heading out.

101
00:06:24,430 --> 00:06:25,120
What kind of urgent matter
is more important

102
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:26,310
than going to school?

103
00:06:26,310 --> 00:06:28,310
Do you realize you are skipping class?

104
00:06:28,310 --> 00:06:29,120
Get inside!

105
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,680
What kind of attitude is that?

106
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:39,810
Apologize to Mr. Bu.

107
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:44,240
I'm sorry, Mr. Bu.

108
00:06:44,310 --> 00:06:45,120
I overslept.

109
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:47,750
You overslept?

110
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:49,120
You made so many people worry about you!

111
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:51,120
And I even rushed back from out of town.

112
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:53,120
How can you be so thoughtless?

113
00:06:53,310 --> 00:06:54,120
Mr. Tong.

114
00:06:54,190 --> 00:06:54,680
Well,

115
00:06:55,430 --> 00:06:56,800
as long as Xiaole is fine,
that's all that matters.

116
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:58,240
Kids at this age

117
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,430
are quite rebellious.

118
00:06:59,430 --> 00:07:00,360
Just talk to him calmly.

119
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:00,890
Alright.

120
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:01,560
I'm leaving first.

121
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,120
Okay.

122
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:04,240
It's fine.

123
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:05,800
Take care.

124
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:15,400
[Pre-filled College Application
Preference Form]

125
00:07:12,430 --> 00:07:13,800
Explain yourself.

126
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,560
Why didn't you fill it in?

127
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:20,750
Didn't I tell you to choose Finance?

128
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:22,120
If I hadn't come back this time,

129
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:24,070
I wouldn't have known
you did something so ridiculous!

130
00:07:24,070 --> 00:07:24,630
You were not even at home.

131
00:07:24,630 --> 00:07:25,310
Who was I supposed to ask?

132
00:07:25,310 --> 00:07:26,360
Couldn't you have called?

133
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:28,240
Like you ever answer your phone?

134
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:29,920
Fine.

135
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:32,120
You don't want to choose Finance.

136
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:34,450
Then tell me
what major you want to choose.

137
00:07:37,870 --> 00:07:38,310
Okay.

138
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,560
Since you don't have a major
of your choice,

139
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:41,960
you must choose Finance.

140
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:44,750
Why should I listen to you?

141
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,240
Because I'm your father!

142
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:47,920
You must do what I say!

143
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:51,250
Choose Finance, right?

144
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,000
You want me to choose Finance.

145
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,240
Isn't it just because you want me
to become like you,

146
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:56,190
spending every single day chasing money?

147
00:07:56,190 --> 00:07:58,120
Is that how you talk to your father?

148
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,000
You ungrateful brat!

149
00:08:14,430 --> 00:08:15,360
Xiaole.

150
00:08:17,310 --> 00:08:18,480
Are you okay?

151
00:08:18,870 --> 00:08:20,730
I've been looking for you all day.

152
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:32,909
Sir,

153
00:08:32,909 --> 00:08:33,870
I'm begging you.

154
00:08:33,870 --> 00:08:34,789
My partner isn't here yet.

155
00:08:34,789 --> 00:08:36,240
This performance is very important to me.

156
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,320
It's important to everyone!

157
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,669
Can't you see everyone's already waiting?

158
00:08:38,669 --> 00:08:39,789
Just give me a little more time, please.

159
00:08:39,789 --> 00:08:41,630
No! Let go!

160
00:08:41,630 --> 00:08:42,690
He'll be here soon.

161
00:08:42,750 --> 00:08:43,750
Get off the stage!

162
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:46,150
Microphone.

163
00:08:47,390 --> 00:08:48,120
Microphone.

164
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:49,670
Give it to me.

165
00:08:58,910 --> 00:09:01,200
Alright, just go.

166
00:09:19,910 --> 00:09:21,320
Honestly, your dad is really something.

167
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,390
He's way out of line!

168
00:09:22,390 --> 00:09:23,670
It's bad enough
that he usually doesn't care about you.

169
00:09:23,670 --> 00:09:25,550
Now he's deciding everything for you!

170
00:09:25,550 --> 00:09:27,320
What's wrong with asking him to come back?

171
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:28,440
He got to have you without any pain,

172
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:29,320
and raise you without any effort.

173
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,390
That's just not right!

174
00:09:30,390 --> 00:09:31,670
How can he get such a free ride?

175
00:09:31,670 --> 00:09:32,730
Don't you think so?

176
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,200
All right.

177
00:09:35,270 --> 00:09:37,330
Stay out of my business. Just go home.

178
00:09:37,790 --> 00:09:40,030
You're always meddling in my business.

179
00:09:40,030 --> 00:09:42,160
Now I can't have a say in your business?

180
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:45,150
You didn't come to school today.

181
00:09:45,150 --> 00:09:46,880
I was worried about you all day.

182
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:52,670
What's there to worry about?

183
00:09:52,670 --> 00:09:53,960
I just overslept.

184
00:09:58,910 --> 00:10:00,200
About your major,

185
00:10:00,670 --> 00:10:01,800
what's in your mind?

186
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,030
Tell me.

187
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,600
If someone really important to you

188
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,530
has all these expectations of you,

189
00:10:10,910 --> 00:10:12,790
then you have to live up
to their expectations

190
00:10:12,790 --> 00:10:14,320
until you leave this world.

191
00:10:15,270 --> 00:10:17,150
Is a life like that even meaningful?

192
00:10:17,150 --> 00:10:18,790
How is it not meaningful?

193
00:10:18,910 --> 00:10:20,570
Living itself is meaningful.

194
00:10:20,910 --> 00:10:23,440
Your existence is meaningful to me.

195
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:26,150
You are the grand prize in my life.

196
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:29,200
I promise I won't leave you.

197
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:32,050
You are really important to me.

198
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:34,320
What do you mean?

199
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,320
You're my family.

200
00:10:38,550 --> 00:10:39,390
Family.

201
00:10:41,790 --> 00:10:42,790
Family.

202
00:10:46,030 --> 00:10:47,840
Talk to your dad properly.

203
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:48,840
Same for me.

204
00:10:49,510 --> 00:10:52,080
We both need to work hard
for what we want.

205
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:53,910
That's what you told me.

206
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:57,370
Are you getting emotional?

207
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,030
Yeah,

208
00:11:00,550 --> 00:11:01,320
I am.

209
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:03,390
Why are you so good to me?

210
00:11:04,670 --> 00:11:06,530
Do I need a reason to be good to you?

211
00:11:06,790 --> 00:11:09,600
Aren't you super good to me too?

212
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:16,840
Yi Lan.

213
00:11:17,270 --> 00:11:18,080
Hmm?

214
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:22,840
What's up?

215
00:11:24,670 --> 00:11:25,200
About what you just said,

216
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,330
promise you mean it.

217
00:11:26,790 --> 00:11:28,320
Of course I mean it.

218
00:11:28,790 --> 00:11:30,550
Pinky promise,

219
00:11:30,670 --> 00:11:31,720
no take backs.

220
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:36,840
Didn't Chen Fan say
you have a performance tonight?

221
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:37,700
What time is it?

222
00:11:42,490 --> 00:11:43,970
[HAVE FUN MUSIC]

223
00:11:42,550 --> 00:11:43,390
Chen Fan!

224
00:11:43,970 --> 00:11:45,670
[When the sun goes down,
it's time to drink]

225
00:11:44,790 --> 00:11:45,790
What took you so long?

226
00:11:45,790 --> 00:11:46,840
What happened?

227
00:11:48,390 --> 00:11:49,320
I left home late.

228
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:50,740
Let's go in.

229
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:51,720
Go in?

230
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:52,510
What's the point now?

231
00:11:52,510 --> 00:11:54,390
Didn't you tell me you'd be on time?

232
00:11:54,390 --> 00:11:55,790
The boss already kicked me out!

233
00:11:55,790 --> 00:11:57,390
Our show is canceled!

234
00:11:58,630 --> 00:11:59,560
It's no big deal.

235
00:11:59,670 --> 00:12:00,870
We can do it next time.

236
00:12:00,910 --> 00:12:01,510
Let's go.

237
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:02,390
Come on.

238
00:12:02,670 --> 00:12:04,200
What kind of attitude is that?

239
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,870
Why are you talking
like you couldn't care less?

240
00:12:05,870 --> 00:12:08,200
If I knew you didn't care,
I would've replaced you ages ago.

241
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:09,120
Chen Fan!

242
00:12:09,910 --> 00:12:12,310
You know damn well
why we started this band!

243
00:12:12,510 --> 00:12:14,200
We're in senior year now.

244
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:15,840
If you weren't my friend,

245
00:12:15,870 --> 00:12:18,130
I wouldn't waste my time on this with you!

246
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:22,200
Get lost!

247
00:12:22,290 --> 00:12:24,390
[When the sun goes down,
it's time to drink]

248
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:37,270
Dad, I'm back.

249
00:12:37,550 --> 00:12:38,280
You're back.

250
00:12:39,550 --> 00:12:41,410
Wash your hands. Dinner's ready.

251
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:42,720
Dad,

252
00:12:45,550 --> 00:12:48,680
I want to apply for the cello major
at Hailan University.

253
00:12:51,020 --> 00:12:53,230
[Senior Year Cello Practice Schedule]

254
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:52,320
In five months,

255
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:54,910
art students will take the joint exams
and the school-specific exams.

256
00:12:54,910 --> 00:12:57,080
Even if I fail, I can still take
the college entrance exam.

257
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:58,910
I've made up my mind this time.

258
00:12:59,670 --> 00:13:00,440
Dad,

259
00:13:00,670 --> 00:13:03,080
I will do my best to achieve it.

260
00:13:05,150 --> 00:13:05,670
Lan.

261
00:13:07,030 --> 00:13:08,080
Some things

262
00:13:08,510 --> 00:13:10,790
can't be achieved just by working hard.

263
00:13:17,150 --> 00:13:18,390
If you just treat the cello

264
00:13:18,390 --> 00:13:19,750
as your hobby,

265
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:21,480
I will fully support you.

266
00:13:21,790 --> 00:13:23,510
But if you want to make it your major,

267
00:13:23,510 --> 00:13:24,320
I don't agree.

268
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:25,320
Besides,

269
00:13:25,910 --> 00:13:28,080
the cello is not a career path for you.

270
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:29,150
Why?

271
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:32,270
People can make a career out of cello too.

272
00:13:32,270 --> 00:13:33,070
I don't agree.

273
00:13:33,530 --> 00:13:34,560
[Senior Year Cello Practice Schedule]

274
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:48,200
Dad.

275
00:14:02,370 --> 00:14:04,580
[Tong Xiaole's First Choice:
Hailan University, Finance]

276
00:14:22,940 --> 00:14:24,620
[Class 9, Grade 12]

277
00:14:42,270 --> 00:14:43,390
Are you crazy?

278
00:14:43,390 --> 00:14:44,600
Are you looking for trouble?

279
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:46,440
You can't catch it and you blame me?

280
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:47,200
Sorry, then.

281
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:55,900
What's wrong with you two?

282
00:14:56,150 --> 00:14:56,910
Nothing.

283
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:59,700
You're such a clam, not saying anything.

284
00:15:36,510 --> 00:15:38,270
Why are they on bad terms?

285
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:40,320
I totally get what men are thinking.

286
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:41,080
Ask me.

287
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:43,410
Then analyze it from a man's perspective.

288
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:48,910
Maybe they fell out
over a misunderstanding

289
00:15:49,270 --> 00:15:50,200
or a conflict.

290
00:16:01,790 --> 00:16:02,600
Or maybe

291
00:16:03,550 --> 00:16:06,910
they got into a fierce competition

292
00:16:07,550 --> 00:16:10,150
over some important resource
or opportunity.

293
00:16:10,790 --> 00:16:12,200
There is another possibility.

294
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:13,440
One of them

295
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:17,390
developed some kind of special feelings
for the other,

296
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:21,790
but couldn't express them openly.

297
00:16:46,440 --> 00:16:47,910
So in this situation,

298
00:16:48,670 --> 00:16:49,790
what should be done?

299
00:16:49,790 --> 00:16:50,440
As men,

300
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:52,370
they just need a fight to settle it.

301
00:16:52,550 --> 00:16:54,080
-A fight?
-A fight.

302
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:57,080
Zhao Zhenghao is good-looking,

303
00:16:57,270 --> 00:16:59,790
but what goes on in his head
is really weird.

304
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:04,069
I've got it.

305
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:20,160
I'm so bored.

306
00:17:20,310 --> 00:17:21,960
How about we play a game?

307
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:23,859
The loser will get flicked

308
00:17:24,109 --> 00:17:25,270
with two fingers.

309
00:17:25,270 --> 00:17:26,109
I'm in! I'm in!

310
00:17:26,829 --> 00:17:27,880
Ning, are you in?

311
00:17:29,110 --> 00:17:30,040
Come on, join us!

312
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:32,920
Interesting.

313
00:17:35,110 --> 00:17:35,960
Me too.

314
00:17:37,790 --> 00:17:39,160
Xiaole, join us!

315
00:17:39,550 --> 00:17:40,310
Childish.

316
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:42,400
Ignore him.

317
00:17:42,550 --> 00:17:43,550
Let's start.

318
00:17:44,030 --> 00:17:45,830
Rock, paper, scissors!

319
00:17:47,510 --> 00:17:48,350
Chen Fan wins.

320
00:17:49,550 --> 00:17:50,350
Go easy, okay?

321
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:54,070
I...

322
00:17:54,110 --> 00:17:55,570
I'll take the punishment.

323
00:17:57,160 --> 00:17:58,000
Wait!

324
00:18:00,550 --> 00:18:01,680
I'll take it for her.

325
00:18:26,310 --> 00:18:27,070
Keep going.

326
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:28,480
Don't be a coward.

327
00:18:34,070 --> 00:18:35,270
Xiaole wins.

328
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:53,070
Alright, alright.

329
00:18:53,070 --> 00:18:54,800
You two stop. It's our turn now.

330
00:18:59,510 --> 00:19:00,550
Xiaole wins.

331
00:19:01,350 --> 00:19:02,480
Xiaole wins.

332
00:19:03,310 --> 00:19:04,960
Still Xiaole wins.

333
00:19:10,790 --> 00:19:12,880
It's our turn. You two stop.

334
00:19:13,240 --> 00:19:14,030
Keep going.

335
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:21,070
Chen Fan wins.

336
00:19:28,790 --> 00:19:29,350
Class is starting.

337
00:19:29,350 --> 00:19:30,350
Stop, stop!

338
00:19:33,110 --> 00:19:34,070
Mr. Bu is here.

339
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:35,000
What are you doing?

340
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,000
Sit down!

341
00:19:40,070 --> 00:19:40,870
Class begins!

342
00:19:42,310 --> 00:19:43,640
It's getting worse.

343
00:20:09,940 --> 00:20:13,120
[Give you my love, from Tong Xiaole]

344
00:20:38,790 --> 00:20:40,720
Tong Xiaole,
is there something wrong with you?

345
00:20:40,720 --> 00:20:43,180
You actually bought me
an expired sandwich!

346
00:20:44,550 --> 00:20:45,350
Are you crazy?

347
00:20:46,030 --> 00:20:47,270
It's expired?

348
00:20:47,750 --> 00:20:50,100
Maybe it went bad
because of the hot weather.

349
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:53,270
[Give you my love, from Chen Fan]

350
00:20:56,980 --> 00:21:01,300
[Give you my love, from Chen Fan]

351
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:38,240
Men...

352
00:21:38,310 --> 00:21:39,830
So complicated.

353
00:22:00,310 --> 00:22:02,570
You don't seem
to be in a good mood lately.

354
00:22:03,790 --> 00:22:04,590
What's wrong?

355
00:22:06,270 --> 00:22:07,270
Nothing.

356
00:22:07,510 --> 00:22:08,790
I was just...

357
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:13,400
thinking about the next performance.

358
00:22:18,480 --> 00:22:19,310
Good luck.

359
00:22:56,790 --> 00:22:57,720
Chen Fan,

360
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:00,160
did you offend Tong Xiaole somehow?

361
00:23:01,310 --> 00:23:02,110
No.

362
00:23:03,270 --> 00:23:04,880
Don't let your little problems

363
00:23:04,880 --> 00:23:06,480
ruin the harmony of our group.

364
00:23:06,480 --> 00:23:08,740
Sort out whatever conflict you two have.

365
00:23:09,310 --> 00:23:11,030
Why is it my problem again?

366
00:23:11,310 --> 00:23:12,750
He's the one with tons of problems,

367
00:23:12,750 --> 00:23:13,810
and he's not loyal.

368
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:14,880
I'm the unlucky one

369
00:23:14,880 --> 00:23:16,680
to have him as a friend, alright?

370
00:23:38,070 --> 00:23:39,600
It must be Chen Fan's fault.

371
00:23:41,790 --> 00:23:43,110
He has already explained himself.

372
00:23:43,110 --> 00:23:44,570
Why don't you believe him?

373
00:25:03,070 --> 00:25:04,310
It hurts.

374
00:25:06,070 --> 00:25:06,930
I didn't expect

375
00:25:07,550 --> 00:25:09,110
you would actually hit me.

376
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:10,790
I'm...

377
00:25:11,720 --> 00:25:12,590
I'm sorry.

378
00:25:27,480 --> 00:25:29,480
I'll be fine after sitting for a bit.

379
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:35,310
Tell me.

380
00:25:36,110 --> 00:25:37,440
What is it really about?

381
00:25:40,510 --> 00:25:41,640
You have no loyalty.

382
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:43,070
You showed up late,

383
00:25:43,350 --> 00:25:44,750
and you looked down on me.

384
00:25:45,510 --> 00:25:47,030
You even hit me.

385
00:25:47,510 --> 00:25:49,550
If I knew you didn't care,
I would've replaced you ages ago.

386
00:25:49,550 --> 00:25:50,590
Chen Fan!

387
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:54,240
What I did the other day counts
as hitting you?

388
00:25:54,240 --> 00:25:55,480
You just hit me too!

389
00:25:55,550 --> 00:25:56,210
We're even.

390
00:25:59,960 --> 00:26:00,720
You're so angry.

391
00:26:00,720 --> 00:26:03,120
Isn't it just
because of that performance?

392
00:26:04,550 --> 00:26:07,480
What do you mean
"just because of that performance"?

393
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:09,000
That performance meant

394
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:10,550
everything to me.

395
00:26:11,070 --> 00:26:11,790
For once,

396
00:26:11,790 --> 00:26:13,030
I finally felt like I was actually useful,

397
00:26:13,030 --> 00:26:14,490
but you didn't care at all!

398
00:26:15,880 --> 00:26:16,830
Chen Fan!

399
00:26:17,960 --> 00:26:19,480
You are very useful!

400
00:26:20,270 --> 00:26:21,200
Useful for what?

401
00:26:23,070 --> 00:26:23,880
You...

402
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:26,960
You...

403
00:26:29,070 --> 00:26:30,030
You...

404
00:26:31,550 --> 00:26:32,830
Your family's villa is very useful.

405
00:26:32,830 --> 00:26:34,550
You know I care about you!

406
00:26:35,880 --> 00:26:37,740
Then why were you late on purpose?

407
00:26:42,350 --> 00:26:44,150
I had a fight with my dad that day.

408
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:50,790
Why didn't you tell me
something so important?

409
00:26:50,790 --> 00:26:51,850
I also care a lot...

410
00:26:53,070 --> 00:26:53,600
about...

411
00:26:54,830 --> 00:26:55,560
your issues.

412
00:27:01,960 --> 00:27:03,400
I care about you too!

413
00:27:03,960 --> 00:27:04,640
Chen Fan!

414
00:27:06,400 --> 00:27:07,310
Xiaole!

415
00:27:14,400 --> 00:27:17,110
Tong Xiaole, you didn't even wait
for me today!

416
00:27:17,310 --> 00:27:18,710
Good morning, everyone.

417
00:27:20,110 --> 00:27:21,240
You two are good now?

418
00:27:21,750 --> 00:27:22,480
What are you talking about?

419
00:27:22,480 --> 00:27:23,790
When did we ever fall out?

420
00:27:23,790 --> 00:27:24,550
Never.

421
00:27:24,790 --> 00:27:25,550
Let's go.

422
00:27:31,350 --> 00:27:32,240
Men...

423
00:27:32,750 --> 00:27:33,720
So complicated.

424
00:27:51,070 --> 00:27:51,720
Shan.

425
00:27:52,350 --> 00:27:53,000
What's up?

426
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:54,200
You seem distracted.

427
00:27:55,160 --> 00:27:56,070
Nothing.

428
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:00,510
I've got a teacher for you.

429
00:28:00,510 --> 00:28:02,310
When will you start practicing?

430
00:28:04,790 --> 00:28:06,680
I haven't convinced my dad yet.

431
00:28:06,960 --> 00:28:08,110
He still doesn't agree.

432
00:28:08,110 --> 00:28:09,310
Still doesn't agree?

433
00:28:11,590 --> 00:28:13,110
Your dad is just...

434
00:28:18,790 --> 00:28:19,640
How about...

435
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:22,350
I go talk to him?

436
00:28:22,550 --> 00:28:23,240
You'll go?

437
00:28:26,510 --> 00:28:27,510
Sure.

438
00:28:28,920 --> 00:28:29,850
When will you go?

439
00:28:31,590 --> 00:28:33,480
Today, I...

440
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:34,200
Tonight!

441
00:28:35,310 --> 00:28:36,030
Tonight?

442
00:28:37,070 --> 00:28:38,880
I've made up my mind.

443
00:28:39,550 --> 00:28:40,880
Don't bring it up again.

444
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:42,640
Please, allow me.

445
00:28:42,640 --> 00:28:43,000
Let me do it.

446
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:43,400
Mr. Yi.

447
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:49,030
Yi Lan

448
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:51,070
has been going to your place a lot lately.

449
00:28:51,070 --> 00:28:52,070
Sorry for the trouble.

450
00:28:52,070 --> 00:28:53,070
No trouble at all.

451
00:28:53,590 --> 00:28:55,650
I like hearing Lan play the cello too.

452
00:28:56,270 --> 00:28:58,130
It always reminds me of my mentor.

453
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:09,030
Your mentor...

454
00:29:10,270 --> 00:29:12,070
She put all her time and energy

455
00:29:12,960 --> 00:29:14,240
into the cello.

456
00:29:16,070 --> 00:29:19,750
She sacrificed everything
to pursue her dream.

457
00:29:38,440 --> 00:29:39,160
So,

458
00:29:40,880 --> 00:29:42,200
I don't want Lan

459
00:29:42,830 --> 00:29:44,230
to end up like her mother.

460
00:29:47,550 --> 00:29:48,550
Have some tea.

461
00:29:48,880 --> 00:29:49,740
Thanks, Mr. Yi.

462
00:29:52,720 --> 00:29:53,520
I understand.

463
00:29:55,030 --> 00:29:55,510
But...

464
00:29:56,310 --> 00:29:57,640
But don't you think...

465
00:29:59,960 --> 00:30:00,830
that now you're

466
00:30:02,310 --> 00:30:03,590
not so different

467
00:30:04,240 --> 00:30:05,840
from how my mentor used to be?

468
00:30:08,400 --> 00:30:09,400
When Yi Lan was little,

469
00:30:09,400 --> 00:30:11,640
my mentor forced her
to practice the cello.

470
00:30:11,640 --> 00:30:12,510
Now she has grown up,

471
00:30:12,510 --> 00:30:14,750
and you won't let her practice the cello.

472
00:30:14,750 --> 00:30:16,550
She's like a fish in your tank.

473
00:30:17,070 --> 00:30:17,790
She eats

474
00:30:17,790 --> 00:30:18,510
whatever you feed her.

475
00:30:18,510 --> 00:30:20,310
Do you really think she's happy?

476
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:25,070
Mr. Yi.

477
00:30:26,640 --> 00:30:28,700
Lately, Lan has been going to my place

478
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:30,790
to practice the cello
every day after school.

479
00:30:30,790 --> 00:30:32,450
Come and see when you're free.

480
00:30:47,110 --> 00:30:47,720
Shan.

481
00:30:48,070 --> 00:30:48,880
How did it go?

482
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:51,110
How did what go?

483
00:30:51,310 --> 00:30:52,240
Did he agree?

484
00:30:54,830 --> 00:30:56,550
Focus on your cello classes first.

485
00:30:56,550 --> 00:30:57,550
We'll talk about it later.

486
00:30:57,550 --> 00:30:57,920
Go in.

487
00:31:03,160 --> 00:31:04,550
Did he agree or not?

488
00:31:06,030 --> 00:31:07,360
We'll discuss it later.

489
00:31:12,480 --> 00:31:13,590
Lan, you're back.

490
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:15,860
I made braised pork for you today.

491
00:31:16,750 --> 00:31:17,270
Dad.

492
00:31:19,270 --> 00:31:20,400
Why won't you agree?

493
00:31:21,310 --> 00:31:22,830
Let's talk after dinner,

494
00:31:23,030 --> 00:31:23,550
okay?

495
00:31:23,830 --> 00:31:25,480
All you ever do is cook for me.

496
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:27,930
You're afraid I'll end up like Mom,

497
00:31:28,510 --> 00:31:29,170
aren't you?

498
00:31:31,550 --> 00:31:33,950
After Mom left,
you never even mention her.

499
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:36,130
And now you won't let me play the cello.

500
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:37,550
Is it because in your heart,

501
00:31:37,550 --> 00:31:39,480
you no longer have a place for my mom?

502
00:31:39,480 --> 00:31:40,550
What nonsense are you talking about?

503
00:31:40,550 --> 00:31:43,000
There was nothing wrong
with Mom chasing her dream!

504
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:45,030
And there is nothing wrong
with me loving music.

505
00:31:45,030 --> 00:31:46,430
Whether you agree or not,

506
00:31:46,750 --> 00:31:48,280
I'm going to play the cello.

507
00:31:48,750 --> 00:31:49,960
I will prove it to you.

508
00:32:08,350 --> 00:32:09,880
It's about Yi Lan, isn't it?

509
00:32:10,830 --> 00:32:11,400
Yes.

510
00:32:13,550 --> 00:32:15,070
Lan's father is stubborn.

511
00:32:15,510 --> 00:32:17,640
It will take some time to persuade him.

512
00:32:18,510 --> 00:32:19,110
Oh, right.

513
00:32:19,550 --> 00:32:22,010
I haven't paid for Lan's lessons yet,
right?

514
00:32:22,070 --> 00:32:22,790
Don't worry about it.

515
00:32:22,790 --> 00:32:24,160
The teacher happens
to be a friend of mine.

516
00:32:24,160 --> 00:32:25,620
We can talk about it later.

517
00:32:25,790 --> 00:32:26,880
That won't do.

518
00:32:27,160 --> 00:32:29,690
How can I let her take lessons
without paying?

519
00:32:29,790 --> 00:32:31,790
Tell me how much it is,

520
00:32:31,790 --> 00:32:33,320
and I'll transfer it to you.

521
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:35,860
How about this?

522
00:32:36,160 --> 00:32:37,750
I'll ask the teacher to contact you,

523
00:32:37,750 --> 00:32:39,680
and you two can settle it directly.

524
00:32:40,310 --> 00:32:41,170
That works too.

525
00:32:41,960 --> 00:32:42,960
I'm leaving now.

526
00:32:42,960 --> 00:32:44,000
Okay, rest early.

527
00:32:59,240 --> 00:32:59,790
Xiaole,

528
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:02,200
call me back when you have a moment.

529
00:33:02,480 --> 00:33:04,550
We're out of town
dealing with something urgent.

530
00:33:04,550 --> 00:33:06,550
We'll stay here for a few extra days.

531
00:33:07,350 --> 00:33:07,960
About choosing your major,

532
00:33:07,960 --> 00:33:10,200
if there's really no major
you have your heart set on,

533
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:12,060
consider your dad's suggestion.

534
00:33:12,720 --> 00:33:13,400
Got it.

535
00:33:35,310 --> 00:33:37,400
I hope Mr. Tong can love Xiaole more.

536
00:33:37,720 --> 00:33:40,200
I'd give Xiaole
half of my dad's love for me.

537
00:34:03,270 --> 00:34:04,110
Sweetie,

538
00:34:04,550 --> 00:34:06,310
could you take a break
from practicing today?

539
00:34:06,310 --> 00:34:07,640
You've been practicing for too long.

540
00:34:07,640 --> 00:34:09,040
Don't wear yourself out.

541
00:34:09,630 --> 00:34:11,480
I've made your favorite dish.

542
00:34:11,480 --> 00:34:12,340
I'm not eating!

543
00:34:12,480 --> 00:34:13,760
It's your favorite!

544
00:34:31,590 --> 00:34:33,920
How did you know
I hadn't eaten dinner yet?

545
00:34:45,550 --> 00:34:49,070
Red phoenix. Red phoenix.

546
00:34:49,070 --> 00:34:54,630
Pink phoenix. Pink...
Colorful phoenix. Pink phoenix.

547
00:34:54,760 --> 00:34:55,440
Mr. Yi,

548
00:34:55,550 --> 00:34:57,070
just got back
from dropping your son off at school?

549
00:34:57,070 --> 00:34:57,760
Come on,

550
00:34:58,190 --> 00:34:58,710
let's play a couple rounds.

551
00:34:58,710 --> 00:34:59,640
A couple rounds.

552
00:35:00,440 --> 00:35:01,670
Your daughter's

553
00:35:01,840 --> 00:35:02,760
voice...

554
00:35:03,150 --> 00:35:04,280
She sounds amazing.

555
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:05,590
Come on.

556
00:35:06,480 --> 00:35:07,150
Of course.

557
00:35:07,710 --> 00:35:08,970
With a voice like that,

558
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:12,110
she's gonna be on TV someday!

559
00:35:13,280 --> 00:35:14,360
TV?

560
00:35:14,630 --> 00:35:15,440
What's wrong with that?

561
00:35:15,440 --> 00:35:16,400
Impressive.

562
00:35:16,920 --> 00:35:18,230
I see your daughter playing

563
00:35:18,230 --> 00:35:20,030
the cello or whatever every day.

564
00:35:20,360 --> 00:35:22,510
Is she planning
to take the art exam too?

565
00:35:22,510 --> 00:35:24,510
That's a tough path to take.

566
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:26,150
Don't worry.

567
00:35:26,360 --> 00:35:27,550
Back in the day, her mom

568
00:35:27,550 --> 00:35:30,000
was the top student in the cello major.

569
00:35:30,630 --> 00:35:32,000
If my daughter wants to take the art exam,

570
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:33,880
it'll be a piece of cake!

571
00:35:34,550 --> 00:35:35,410
Let me tell you.

572
00:35:35,710 --> 00:35:36,880
Time is running out.

573
00:35:37,030 --> 00:35:37,960
For the art exam,

574
00:35:38,030 --> 00:35:40,280
everyone is already getting
private tutors.

575
00:35:40,280 --> 00:35:41,760
Your daughter still goes
to regular school every day.

576
00:35:41,760 --> 00:35:43,190
You think she can make it?

577
00:35:43,440 --> 00:35:44,400
Mr. Yi,

578
00:35:44,400 --> 00:35:45,670
it seems like

579
00:35:45,710 --> 00:35:46,840
you don't care

580
00:35:46,960 --> 00:35:48,550
about your daughter at all.

581
00:35:51,070 --> 00:35:51,760
Come on,

582
00:35:52,360 --> 00:35:53,220
another round.

583
00:35:54,710 --> 00:35:55,110
I need to take this call.

584
00:35:55,110 --> 00:35:55,970
Another round.

585
00:35:59,070 --> 00:36:00,070
Such a sore loser.

586
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:04,070
Shan.

587
00:36:05,510 --> 00:36:08,040
Do you still remember
what my mom looked like?

588
00:36:09,480 --> 00:36:10,030
I do.

589
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:11,710
Although

590
00:36:12,400 --> 00:36:13,800
my memory of her face

591
00:36:14,510 --> 00:36:16,400
is already blurry,

592
00:36:17,920 --> 00:36:19,000
I always feel

593
00:36:19,320 --> 00:36:20,840
that if she were still here,

594
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:22,230
she would definitely support me

595
00:36:22,230 --> 00:36:23,760
in doing what I want to do.

596
00:36:24,070 --> 00:36:24,800
Your dad

597
00:36:25,190 --> 00:36:27,990
really shouldn't stop you
from playing the cello.

598
00:36:28,150 --> 00:36:29,000
He probably

599
00:36:29,630 --> 00:36:31,280
hasn't made peace with himself yet.

600
00:36:31,280 --> 00:36:32,940
You need to give him some time.

601
00:36:33,840 --> 00:36:35,360
But you're the one

602
00:36:37,190 --> 00:36:38,630
who decides your own life.

603
00:36:38,630 --> 00:36:41,090
It has nothing to do
with your mom or your dad.

604
00:36:41,190 --> 00:36:43,790
So you really need
to think about it carefully.

605
00:37:17,070 --> 00:37:18,230
Xiaole!

606
00:37:25,070 --> 00:37:26,400
Xiaole!

607
00:37:27,360 --> 00:37:30,110
My dad agreed to let me take the art exam!

608
00:37:31,540 --> 00:37:34,210
♪ She left in spring ♪

609
00:37:34,850 --> 00:37:38,170
♪ All was like a dream ♪

610
00:37:38,520 --> 00:37:41,210
♪ Youth never lasts ♪

611
00:37:42,060 --> 00:37:45,510
♪ Just let her go ♪

612
00:37:45,700 --> 00:37:48,160
♪ The paper plane that was once set free ♪

613
00:37:48,340 --> 00:37:49,530
♪ Will find its way back
to the old desk and chair at school ♪
